    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-01T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-01T08:00:00-05:00" n="57"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the the United
                        Nations</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-01T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 1, 1951—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 459. Subject: <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                        >SC</gloss> elections. Re developments Latin Amer caucus as result our
                        <gloss target="#t_ICJ1">ICJ</gloss> position reported <gloss
                        target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 448, <gloss target="#t_USGADel1"
                        >USGADel</gloss> staff recommends circular instruction to Latin Amer
                    capitals reiterating importance we attach to rejection of Sov satellite
                    Byelorussian candidacy for <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>. This shld be
                    stated in affirmative form of reaffirmation of reasons for this position and of
                    our support for Greece as principal candidate for this seat. Circular shld
                    express hope <gloss target="#t_del1">del</gloss>s will be instructed to take
                    similar position in <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> elections next week.</p>
                <p>Strong conviction of <gloss target="#t_USGADel1">USGADel</gloss> staff that we
                    must maintain our position re <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> election and
                    this will be recommended <gloss target="#t_USGADel1">USGADel</gloss> in
                    reporting present sitn on Mon morning.</p>
                <p>Holmes<note n="1" xml:id="d57fn1">Julius C. Holmes, Minister of Embassy in the
                        United Kingdom.</note> at our request has talked to officer in charge of
                        <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> today, Dixon,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d57fn2">Sir Pierson Dixon, British Deputy Under Secretary of State
                        for Foreign Affairs.</note> and indicated our serious concern over this
                    sitn. These views will be communicated to Eden who is away from London for
                    weekend. Dixon thought Jebb might have instructions by tomorrow night.</p>
                <p>At our suggestion Bonsal<note n="3" xml:id="d57fn3">Philip W. Bonsal, Counselor
                        of Embassy in France.</note> talked this morning with De La Tournelle<note
                        n="4" xml:id="d57fn4">Guy de La Tournelle, Director-General of Political and
                        Economic Affairs, French Ministry for Foreign Affairs.</note> and found Fr
                    surprisingly categorical on supporting Byelorussia. He admitted they thought
                    they had probably “corrupted” Brit on this score. Bonsal reiterated importance
                    we attach to supporting Greece and rejecting Sov satellite Byelorussia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
